          <LEXSenses>
            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2021-06-02 17:29:43" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>to serve God in some special way, such as a deacon</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>to be a deacon</Gloss>
                <Gloss>to minister to</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>It seems quite evident that διακονέω[d] involved a number of different functions as persons served others, especially in connection with relief to the poor. In some instances it may be best to translate διακονέω[d] as ‘to have responsibility to help others’ or ‘to be responsible to take care of the needs of believers.’</Comments>
            </LEXSense>
